$ Specifying a characterset within an HTML document

The encoding of → development/web/HTML[HTML] document can be specified with the → development/web/HTML/tags/meta[<meta> tag].

The following example sets it to utf8:
code {
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html><head>

  <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">

</head></html>
code }

sa:
  → development/web/HTML/tags/meta

  → development/Unicode/character-set

  → development/Unicode/character-encoding
